### Integration Framework API Tests
### Test file for integration management endpoints
### Requires: auth.http to be run first (sets @token and @tenantId variables)

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8080/api
@contentType = application/json

### 1. Get all integrations (empty initially)
GET {{baseUrl}}/integrations
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 2. Create Slack integration
POST {{baseUrl}}/integrations
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "adapterType": "slack",
  "name": "Sales Channel",
  "enabled": true,
  "credentials": {
    "webhookUrl": "https://hooks.slack.com/services/YOUR/WEBHOOK/URL"
  },
  "eventTypes": "CUSTOMER_CREATED,OPPORTUNITY_UPDATED"
}

### 3. Create webhook integration with HMAC secret
POST {{baseUrl}}/integrations
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "adapterType": "webhook",
  "name": "Production Webhook",
  "enabled": true,
  "credentials": {
    "url": "https://webhook.example.com/crm-events",
    "secret": "your-hmac-secret-key"
  },
  "eventTypes": "CUSTOMER_CREATED,CUSTOMER_UPDATED,CONTACT_CREATED"
}

### 4. Create HubSpot integration
POST {{baseUrl}}/integrations
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "adapterType": "hubspot",
  "name": "HubSpot Production",
  "enabled": true,
  "credentials": {
    "apiKey": "pat-na1-your-hubspot-api-key"
  },
  "eventTypes": "CUSTOMER_CREATED,CUSTOMER_UPDATED,CONTACT_CREATED"
}

### 5. Create Zapier integration (subscribe to ALL events)
POST {{baseUrl}}/integrations
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "adapterType": "zapier",
  "name": "Zapier Workflows",
  "enabled": true,
  "credentials": {
    "webhookUrl": "https://hooks.zapier.com/hooks/catch/YOUR/ID"
  },
  "eventTypes": ""
}

### 6. List all integrations
GET {{baseUrl}}/integrations
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 7. Get specific integration (ID from response above)
### Replace {id} with actual integration ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/integrations/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 8. Update integration (enable/disable, change events)
### Replace {id} with actual integration ID
PUT {{baseUrl}}/integrations/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "adapterType": "slack",
  "name": "Sales Channel - Updated",
  "enabled": false,
  "credentials": {
    "webhookUrl": "https://hooks.slack.com/services/YOUR/WEBHOOK/URL"
  },
  "eventTypes": "CUSTOMER_CREATED,CUSTOMER_UPDATED"
}

### 9. Test webhook manually with curl
### curl -X POST https://webhook.example.com/crm-events \
###   -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
###   -H "X-Signature: sha256=<hmac>" \
###   -d '{"eventType":"CRM_EVENT","entityType":"Customer",...}'

### 10. Delete integration
### Replace {id} with actual integration ID
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/integrations/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ─── Integration Event Testing ─────────────────────────────────────

### Create a customer to trigger CUSTOMER_CREATED event
POST {{baseUrl}}/customers
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Integration Test Corp",
  "status": "active",
  "customFields": {}
}

### Update the customer to trigger CUSTOMER_UPDATED event
### Replace {customerId} with ID from response above
PUT {{baseUrl}}/customers/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Integration Test Corp - Updated",
  "status": "qualified"
}

### Delete the customer to trigger CUSTOMER_DELETED event
### Replace {customerId} with ID from above
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/customers/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### ─── Webhook Testing (using webhook.site) ─────────────────────────

### 1. Visit https://webhook.site and copy your unique URL
### 2. Create webhook integration with that URL
### 3. Create/update/delete a customer in BOCRM
### 4. Check webhook.site to see the POST request from IntegrationPoller
### 5. Verify payload structure matches expected format

### ─── Debugging: Check OutboxEvent Status ──────────────────────────

### Query to see pending events (requires direct DB access)
### SELECT * FROM outbox_events
### WHERE event_type = 'CRM_EVENT' AND published_at IS NULL
### ORDER BY created_at DESC LIMIT 10;

### High retry count indicates delivery failure
### SELECT id, adapter_type, retry_count, created_at
### FROM outbox_events
### WHERE published_at IS NULL AND retry_count > 3
### ORDER BY retry_count DESC;

